le": "partner", "role_id": 575, "is_primary": false}, {"id": 2642270, "title": "Where is my story?", "work_id": 110869, "role": "partner", "role_id": 575, "is_primary": false}, {"id": 3110268, "title": "Love n' life knows no end", "work_id": 110870, "role": "partner", "role_id": 575, "is_primary": false}, {"id": 2711132, "title": "Testimony: a story machine", "work_id": 109017, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": null, "date_of_death": null, "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "RMIT University, officially the Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology, is a public research university in Melbourne, Australia.\r\nFounded in 1887 by Francis Ormond, RMIT began as a night school offering classes in art, science and technology in response to the industrial revolution in Australia. It was a private college for more than a hundred years before merging with the Phillip Institute of Technology to become a public university in 1992. It has an enrolment of around 95,000 higher and vocational education students, making it the largest dual-sector education institution in Australia. With an annual revenue of around A$1.5 billion, it is also one of the wealthiest universities in Australia. It is rated a five star university by Quacquarelli Symonds (QS) and is ranked 15th in the World for art and design subjects in the QS World University Rankings, making it the top art and design university in Australia and Oceania.\r\nThe main campus of RMIT is situated on the northern edge of the historic Hoddle Grid in the city centre of Melbourne. It has two satellite campuses in the city's northern suburbs of Brunswick and Bundoora and a training site situated on the RAAF Williams base in the western suburb of Point Cook. It also has a training site at Bendigo Airport in the Victorian city of Bendigo and a research site in  Hamilton near the Grampians National Park. In Asia, it has two branch campuses in Ho Chi Minh City and Hanoi and a training centre in Da Nang in Vietnam as well as teaching partnerships in Mainland China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Singapore and Sri Lanka. In Europe, it has a research and collaboration centre in the Spanish city of Barcelona.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-06T00:37:04+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 6137, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RMIT_University"}], "uuid": "5cf71182-a749-4621-ba5b-66d2fa0039db", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110235", "external_references": [{"id": 51923, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q1057890"}, {"id": 55660, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "262196396"}, {"id": 55661, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n50069414"}, {"id": 55662, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n50069414"}], "date_modified": "2025-12-17T14:35:13.289301+11:00"}, {"id": 9096, "name": "Simon Norton", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2711131, "title": "Testimony: a story machine", "work_id": 109017, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": null, "date_of_death": null, "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Simon Norton is a multimedia artist who works in many areas, including writing, animation, comics, sound collage, and web design. He has studied film, writing, painting, audio engineering and multimedia. He is principally interested in ideas and concept-driven works, and exploring the potentials of interactive fiction, interactive comics and interactive iconography.\n\"Testimony: A Story Machine\" won a place in the New talent Competition at MILIA 2002, Cannes, France, won the Megabite Digital Film Project at Next Wave Festival 2002, Melbourne Australia, won Best Short in the web category at I Castelli Animati International Animated Film Festival 7th Edition 2002 in Rome Italy, won second place in the Interactive Storytelling category at Mecon in Cologne, Germany, was part of the Prototype exhibition at the Victorian Arts Centre and was a finalist in several other website competitions", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-11T23:46:52.599279+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "f77203ad-fa38-41e1-9774-3ce3f98bf86c", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111998", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:46:52.599598+11:00"}, {"id": 9095, "name": "Paul Brown", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2711127, "title": "Chromos", "work_id": 109016, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1807318, "title": "Arguing the Toss of a Cat", "work_id": 79247, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2711129, "title": "Chromos", "work_id": 109016, "role": "visual artist", "role_id": 493, "is_primary": false}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Paul Brown is an artist and writer who has been specialising in art and technology for 30 years. His computer-generated artwork has been exhibited internationally since 1967, and he has held a variety of academic and artist-in-residence positions in the USA, the UK and Australia.\n full details available at\nwww.paul-brown.com", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-11T23:46:51.652121+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "8aff9009-3c0e-418b-8773-418923873e94", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111993", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:46:51.652438+11:00"}, {"id": 9094, "name": "Ian Andrews", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2751405, "title": "Physical education activities for the classroom", "work_id": 97794, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 863504, "title